    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix SgNB Release Request Generation for NSA UEs\n\n### Summary\nThe `rrc_generate_SgNBReleaseRequest` function was commented out and had incomplete implementation. When called, it would not send proper X2AP messages to release the SgNB connection for NSA UEs.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: Uncommented and fully implemented `rrc_generate_SgNBReleaseRequest` function with proper X2AP message population\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_proto.h`: Added function declaration\n- `openair2/RRC/LTE/rrc_eNB.c`: Uncommented call to the function in `rrc_eNB_generate_RRCConnectionRelease`\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen an NSA UE is released via RRC Connection Release, the SgNB release request is not sent to the gNB, causing the UE to remain connected to the gNB. This can be observed by:\n1. Establishing an EN-DC connection with an NSA UE\n2. Triggering RRC Connection Release from the eNB\n3. Monitoring X2AP traffic - no SgNB Release Request message is sent\n4. The gNB continues to maintain the UE context until timeout\n\nThe fix ensures that when `rrc_generate_SgNBReleaseRequest()` is called for NSA UEs in RRC_NR_NSA or RRC_NR_NSA_RECONFIGURED states, a proper X2AP_ENDC_SGNB_RELEASE_REQUEST message is sent to the gNB with the correct UE RNTI, association ID, and cause.\n"
}